    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-16T10:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-16T10:48:00-05:00" n="645"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/10034</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CCB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-16T10:00:00-05:48">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 17, 6.25 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In the course of a conversation yesterday afternoon I intimated to the President
                    that the position of Honduras as to claims by Germany after the war would be
                    stronger if it declared war and he said <pb facs="0782" n="690" xml:id="pg_690"
                    /> that he was only awaiting the return of the Minister for Foreign Affairs who
                    has been ill for about two months to ask for a report as to the international
                    law on the subject. I suggest that you have prepared and send me a memorandum
                    along these lines citing authorities with editions and pages.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
